# MedAssist AI — Master Implementation Roadmap v2.0
## From Prototype → Production-Grade AI Medical Operating System

> **Codebase Audit Complete.** 17 feature modules, 9 repositories, 2 services, 32+ routes analyzed.
> **CTO Review: APPROVED ✅** — Plan locked for execution with 5 additional enterprise upgrades.

---

## Executive Summary

MedAssist currently has a **functional shell** — 17 feature folders, Supabase integration, NVIDIA NIM AI pipeline, nutrition module, monitoring, and an interactive body map. However, it is held together by mock data, has zero local caching, a weak onboarding flow, and several modules that are either incomplete or redundant.

This roadmap transforms it into a **production-grade AI Medical OS** across **5 execution phases** over ~8-12 weeks.

### v2.0 Additions (CTO Review)
- ✅ Push Notification Infrastructure (Firebase + Local)
- ✅ Audit Logging for medical compliance
- ✅ Storage Versioning for records
- ✅ Feature Flags for safe rollout
- ✅ AI Observability for NIM token/cost tracking
- ✅ **Jitsi Meet locked as Video SDK** (free, open source, Flutter + React compatible)

