### 1.4 — Audit Logging Infrastructure

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **NEW in v2.0** — Medical systems need full action traceability for compliance, debugging, doctor portal visibility, and admin dashboards.

**Supabase Schema — `audit_logs` table:**
```sql
CREATE TABLE audit_logs (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users,
    action_type TEXT NOT NULL,     -- 'report_uploaded', 'doctor_booked', 'payment_success',
                                  -- 'record_shared', 'sos_triggered', 'ocr_extracted',
                                  -- 'profile_updated', 'login', 'logout', 'ai_query'
    module TEXT NOT NULL,          -- 'records', 'doctors', 'sos', 'auth', 'ai', 'vitals'
    entity_id UUID,               -- ID of the affected record/appointment/etc.
    metadata JSONB DEFAULT '{}',  -- Flexible context: {old_value, new_value, ip, device}
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- Index for fast user-scoped queries
CREATE INDEX idx_audit_user ON audit_logs(user_id, created_at DESC);
CREATE INDEX idx_audit_module ON audit_logs(module, created_at DESC);
```

**Flutter Integration:**
```
lib/core/audit/
├── audit_service.dart             # Static AuditService.log(action, module, entityId, metadata)
└── audit_constants.dart           # Typed action_type and module string constants
```

**Usage pattern (every critical action):**
```dart
await AuditService.log(
  action: AuditAction.reportUploaded,
  module: AuditModule.records,
  entityId: recordId,
  metadata: {'file_type': 'blood_test', 'size_kb': 1240},
);
```

