### 1.6 — AI Observability Layer

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **NEW in v2.0** — Track NIM API usage, token consumption, latency, and cost estimates. This saves your budget and provides critical debugging data.

**Supabase Schema — `ai_usage_logs` table:**
```sql
CREATE TABLE ai_usage_logs (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users,
    function_name TEXT NOT NULL,    -- 'symptom-triage', 'ocr-extract', 'doctor-match', etc.
    model_name TEXT,               -- 'nvidia/llama-3.1-nemotron-ultra-253b-v1', etc.
    prompt_tokens INT,
    completion_tokens INT,
    total_tokens INT GENERATED ALWAYS AS (prompt_tokens + completion_tokens) STORED,
    latency_ms INT,
    cost_estimate NUMERIC(10,6),   -- USD estimate per call
    status TEXT DEFAULT 'success', -- 'success', 'error', 'timeout'
    error_message TEXT,
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);

-- Index for cost analytics
CREATE INDEX idx_ai_usage_user ON ai_usage_logs(user_id, created_at DESC);
CREATE INDEX idx_ai_usage_function ON ai_usage_logs(function_name, created_at DESC);
```

