**Supabase Schema — `medical_records` table (with v2.0 versioning):**
```sql
CREATE TABLE medical_records (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users NOT NULL,
    parent_record_id UUID REFERENCES medical_records, -- v2.0: Version chain
    version INT DEFAULT 1,                             -- v2.0: Version number
    category TEXT NOT NULL,        -- 'prescription', 'blood_test', 'imaging', 'discharge', 'other'
    title TEXT NOT NULL,
    file_url TEXT NOT NULL,        -- Supabase Storage URL
    file_type TEXT,                -- 'image/jpeg', 'application/pdf'
    ocr_text TEXT,                 -- Extracted text from OCR
    ai_summary TEXT,               -- AI-generated summary
    extracted_medicines TEXT[],     -- Parsed medicine names
    abnormal_values JSONB,         -- {"hemoglobin": {"value": 9.2, "range": "12-16", "status": "low"}}
    doctor_share_permissions JSONB DEFAULT '[]',
    tags TEXT[] DEFAULT '{}',
    record_date DATE,
    is_latest BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE, -- v2.0: Only latest version shows in UI
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()
);
```

> [!TIP]
> **v2.0 Versioning Logic:** When a user uploads a corrected/updated version of a report, set `parent_record_id` to the original, increment `version`, and set `is_latest = FALSE` on the old record. The UI filters by `is_latest = TRUE` but the detail screen shows the full version chain.

